-------------------------------
  Vivado HLS ESP accelerators
-------------------------------

The ESP templates for a Vivado HLS accelerator can be generated by running the
following command from the ESP home directory:

    $ ESP_ROOT=$PWD ./utils/scripts/init_accelerator.sh <accelerator_name> vivado_hls

At the very minimum the user should then edit the following files to customize the accelerator implementation.

- <accelerator_name>.xml

- inc/espacc_config.h

- syn/custom.tcl

- The compute function in src/espacc.cc

The ESP template implements an accelerator that loads a single input array and
stores a single output array. For more complex load-store behaviors the user
will have to extend the implementation of the generated ESP accelerator
template.

- Additional custom directives should be placed in syn/directives.tcl

- The load, compute and store functions in src/espacc.cc might need
  modifications. The testbench in tb/tb.cc must be modified accordingly.

- Add all new constants and datatypes either in inc/espacc_config.h and inc/espacc.h
